  "prompt": "I got 168 in JEE (Main) 2016. How much score should I expect (rough range) according to my potential , in BITSAT 2016 ?",
  "response": "While it's difficult to predict an exact score for BITSAT based on your JEE Main score, there are some general trends you can consider. BITSAT is known to have a different pattern and level of difficulty compared to JEE Main. \n\nTypically, students who perform well in JEE Main (like getting 168) may have a similar or slightly better performance in BITSAT due to the nature of the exams, but the score can vary significantly based on preparation and familiarity with the exam format.\n\nIf you performed well in JEE Main and are well-prepared for BITSAT, a rough estimate might be that you could aim for a score around 200 to 250 in BITSAT, depending on your preparation, practice with the type of questions asked in BITSAT, and familiarity with its specific syllabus and pattern. However, this is just a rough estimate and can greatly vary from student to student.\n\nIt's important to focus on your preparation and understanding of the subjects to perform to the best of your ability. Good luck!",
